  "local_port": 53360,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I change One Plus 3 ringtone?",
  "response": "Changing the ringtone on your OnePlus 3 is a straightforward process. You can choose from the pre-installed ringtones or set a custom one from your personal collection. Below are step-by-step instructions to help you change your ringtone:\n\n### **Method 1: Using the Settings Menu**\n\n1. **Unlock Your OnePlus 3:**\n   - Ensure your device is powered on and unlocked.\n\n2. **Open the Settings App:**\n   - Locate the **Settings** icon (usually a gear-shaped symbol) in your app drawer or on your home screen and tap to open it.\n\n3. **Navigate to Sound Settings:**\n   - Scroll down and tap on **\"Sound\"** or **\"Sounds & Vibration\"** depending on your OxygenOS version.\n\n4. **Select Ringtone:**\n   - Under the **\"Sound\"** section, tap on **\"Ringtone\"**. This will display a list of available default ringtones.\n\n5. **Choose a Ringtone:**\n   - Browse through the list and tap on the ringtone you wish to set. You'll typically hear a preview when you tap each option.\n   - Once you've found your preferred ringtone, it will be set as your default.\n\n6. **Set a Custom Ringtone (Optional):**\n   - If you want to use a custom ringtone from your device's storage:\n     - Within the **\"Ringtone\"** menu, look for an option like **\"Add ringtone\"**, **\"+\"**, or **\"From phone\"**.\n     - Tap on it and navigate to the audio file you want to use. Common audio formats like MP3 or WAV are usually supported.\n     - Select the desired file, and it will be set as your ringtone.\n\n### **Method 2: Using the Contacts App (Set Ringtone for a Specific Contact)**\n\nIf you want to assign a specific ringtone to a particular contact:\n\n1. **Open the Contacts App:**\n   - Find and open the **Contacts** app on your OnePlus 3.\n\n2. **Select the Contact:**\n   - Choose the contact for whom you want to set a custom ringtone.\n\n3. **Edit Contact Details:**\n   - Tap on the **\"Edit\"** option (often represented by a pencil icon).\n\n4. **Set Ringtone:**\n   - Scroll down to find the **\"Ringtone\"** option.\n   - Tap on it and select the desired ringtone from the list or add a new one from your device storage.\n\n5. **Save Changes:**\n   - After selecting the ringtone, make sure to **save** or **update** the contact to apply the changes.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Adding Custom Ringtones:**\n  - Ensure that any custom ringtone you want to use is saved in the **\"Ringtones\"** folder on your device. You can use a file manager app to place your desired audio files in this folder for easier access when selecting ringtones.\n\n- **Using Third-Party Apps:**\n  - Apps like **Zedge**, **Ringtone Maker**, or **Audiko** can help you download or create custom ringtones directly from the Google Play Store.\n\n- **Volume Settings:**\n  - After changing your ringtone, you might want to adjust the **volume** to ensure it's at a comfortable level. This can also be done from the **\"Sound\"** settings.\n\nBy following these steps, you can easily customize the ringtone on your OnePlus 3 to suit your preferences. If you encounter any issues or have further questions, feel free to ask!",
